Course.name: Gunnery Engagement Exemplar - Playback
Course.description:
This course contains DKFs that can be used to test the issues and tasks being worked under Task #5279 for improvements to the NCSUTeamCoach branch. 


It is recommended that each DKF be used independently - users should manually disable/enable the VBS course objects as needed before starting the course.

message.content:
Welcome to the ï»¿Gunnery Engagement Exemplar GIFT Course

This course is designed to accompany the GIFT 2023-1 Official Release.  This course provides a playback of a training scenario that was conducted using Virtual Battle Space (VBS) and showcases several of the new features that were introduced in this release.


In order to run this course, you'll need to configure GIFT to use the Example Strategy Provider tool that is packaged with the release.

To do this, follow the steps below:

  1. Open GIFT/config/common.properties and remove the # character next to the ExternalStrategyProviderUrl property near the bottom of the file.
    •     
  2. Run GIFT\scripts\dev-tools\exampleStrategyProvider\runExampleStrategyProvider.bat. A console window should appear and display a message stating that the external strategy provider is running.


The intention of this course is to showcase new features to the GIFT community. You will be presented with a message that covers these new features in detail after the playback concludes. More information on GIFT features can also be found in the link above.

In addition to configuring the example strategy provider, you will need to open GIFT's Game Master in a separate browser tab in order to finish the course, since the last portion requires interaction from an observer controller/trainer (OC/T).


To access the Game Master, sign into GIFT normally and then click "Game Master" at the top of the webpage, followed by "Active Sessions".


Once the arrow button above is pressed, you can view the running session by clicking on it in the Game Master webpage.


Throughout the playback, you will see a series of messages in the panel on the left.

Messages in bold are directed toward you, while messages not in bold are directed at the learners that originally completed the actions in VBS.

During the third and final engagement of the course, you will see a message prompting you to open Game Master and provide assessments for a few of the remaining concepts.


To do this, you will first need to open the Assessments panel. If it is not already showing, you can display it using either of the two buttons above the center map area.



Once the Assessments panel is open, you will want to look for black stars with yellow blinking backgrounds behind them and then click on one of the black stars to provide an assessment. There are 6 of these sets of stars in total that need to have assessments provided to them.

Once all 6 of these assessments have been provided, the final feedback message will be shown, and course will end shortly thereafter.

Thank you for taking the course.

Throughout the playback of this course, you observed the following new features from this release:

  • Displaying strategy activities based on suggestions from an external strategy provider
  • Using an external strategy provider to customize how details from a training session are shown
  • Moving between multiple training sessions automatically, both for learners and for OC/Ts in Game Master
  • Assessing whether learners in a vehicle detected one or more targets
  • Waiting to invoke an instructional strategy until after an OC/T has provided multiple required assessments

If you are interested in saving the details of the automated assessments that occurred during this course, such as how quickly the targets were eliminated or when they were shown, please refer to the release documentation on gifttutoring.org for additional details.
